@@ -0,0 +1,98 @@
+# Pala OS V6 Source Stamp Contract
+
+Status: `RELEASE_BLOCKED`
+
+This contract defines the Phase A source-court audit rules. It is audit-mode
+only until the owner explicitly approves enforce-mode.
+
+## Classification Semantics
+
+| Class | Meaning | Release evidence |
+| --- | --- | --- |
+| `PALA_ORIGINAL` | Active V6 material written for this repo. | Allowed when validator links it. |
+| `LEGACY_ADAPTED` | Active material adapted from old Pala sources. | Allowed only with the full source chain. |
+| `OSS_ADAPTED` | Active material adapted from an external OSS source. | Allowed only with source card and court decision; code adaptations also need a stamp. |
+| `REFERENCE_ONLY` | Historical or contextual material. | Never release evidence. |
+| `GOVERNANCE_DOC` | Material that can affect court, release, gate, or agent behavior. | Tracked as governance influence; adapted docs need the source chain. |
+
+`README.md`, `AGENTS.md`, `PALA_RULES.md`, `SECURITY.md`,
+`ARCHITECTURE.md`, court decisions, release-gate documents, and governance
+documents are never treated as automatic `REFERENCE_ONLY` material.
+
+## Required Source Stamp Fields
+
+```ts
+/**
+ * @palaSourceRef <source-url-or-path>
+ * @palaSourceRepo <repo-or-local-archive>
+ * @palaCourtDecision <ADAPT|ADOPT|IMPORT_LATER|QUARANTINE|REJECT>
+ * @palaCourtId <court-id>
+ * @palaRewritePolicy <short rewrite policy>
+ * @palaSavedEstimate <estimate-or-NOT_AVAILABLE_WITH_REASON>
+ */
+```
+
+`LEGACY_ADAPTED` active material always requires a source stamp.
+`OSS_ADAPTED` code adaptations require a source stamp. OSS pattern-only
+material still requires a source card and court decision.
+
+## Source Card Minimum Fields
+
+A source card must carry:
+
+- origin type and origin ref
+- repo or local archive path
+- visibility
+- commit, local archive ref, or explicit unavailable reason
+- license or `NOT_AVAILABLE_WITH_REASON`
+- court decision
+- risk level
+- allowed layer
+- summary or evidence URI
+
+Source cards alone do not produce `PASS`.
+
+## Court Decision Requirement
+
+Adapted active material must match a court decision. The validator accepts
+court decisions from the machine-readable inheritance backlog or future source
+court records. The decision must identify the source family and carry an
+allowed court decision such as `ADAPT`, `ADOPT`, `IMPORT_LATER`,
+`QUARANTINE`, or `REJECT`.
+
+## Verdict Rules
+
+`PASS` is allowed only when the required chain is complete:
+
+1. Source stamp when required.
+2. Source card.
+3. Court decision.
+4. Validator link.
+5. Required fields complete.
+
+`BLOCKED` is returned when adapted active material is missing any required
+chain item.
+
+`PARTIAL` is reserved for non-release-blocking audit states such as
+governance tracking or reference-only material.
+
+`NOT_AVAILABLE_WITH_REASON` is returned when a configured source-court scope
+cannot be inspected or when there are no active source-court files.
+
+## Governance Docs Versus Reference Material
+
+`GOVERNANCE_DOC` material can influence agent behavior, release decisions,
+court decisions, source-card rules, or gate wording. It is tracked even when it
+is Pala-original.
+
+`REFERENCE_ONLY` material preserves historical context. It cannot satisfy a
+release gate and cannot make the dashboard green.
+
+## Audit Mode And Future Enforce Mode
+
+Phase A runs in audit-mode. Audit-mode reports source-chain gaps and exposes
+`sourceStampGate` in court output. It does not delete legacy material, rewrite
+source cards, push to GitHub, or approve release.
+
+Future enforce-mode may block release automatically when `sourceStampGate` is
+`BLOCKED`. Owner approval is required before enforce-mode is activated.
